abstract: >-
  pyrxiv is a Python package for retrieving arXiv papers,
  storing their metadata in pydantic-like classes, and
  optionally filtering some of them out based on the
  specific content of the papers (matching a regex
  pattern). While originally developed for the Strongly
  Correlated Electron Systems community in Condensed
  Matter Physics (cond-mat.str-el), it's designed to be
  flexible and applicable to any arXiv category.
